(Assignment 03 Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Building Graph Representation and Node Classification) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Course: Graph Machine Learning) Tj
T*
(Assignment: Assignment 03, Building Graph Representation) Tj
T*
(Date: 8 June 2026) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Abstract) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This assignment converts a Rhino-exported architectural model into a Building) Tj
T*
(Graph Representation \(BGR\) and uses it for graph machine learning. Four OBJ) Tj
T*
(files represent the main semantic layers of the building: ground slab,) Tj
T*
(columns, office volumes, and core. These parts are imported into TopologicPy,) Tj
T*
(converted into topological cells, labelled with semantic dictionaries, merged) Tj
T*
(into a CellComplex, and transformed into an adjacency graph. The exported) Tj
T*
(BGR contains one graph, 55 nodes, and 286 directed edge records. Because graph) Tj
T*
(classification requires many building graphs, the single exported building is) Tj
T*
(instead used for node classification. A node-classification dataset is derived) Tj
T*
(from the BGR, mapping the original cell types to contiguous labels and using) Tj
T*
(normalised node coordinates as features. The resulting model demonstrates the) Tj
T*
(complete workflow from geometry to graph dataset, training, evaluation, and) Tj
T*
(model export.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Introduction) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Architectural geometry contains both shape and relationship. A building can be) Tj
T*
(modelled as a set of volumes, but it can also be represented as a graph whose) Tj
T*
(nodes describe spatial or construction elements and whose edges describe) Tj
T*
(adjacency. This graph representation makes the model suitable for graph) Tj
T*
(machine learning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The aim of this assignment is to:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Import a layered Rhino OBJ model into TopologicPy.) Tj
T*
(2. Assign semantic categories to each building component.) Tj
T*
(3. Build a merged topological model and convert it into a graph.) Tj
T*
(4. Export the graph as CSV files.) Tj
T*
(5. Train a graph machine learning workflow on the exported data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The initial assignment notebook was graph-classification oriented. However,) Tj
T*
(only one building graph was exported. Since graph classification requires) Tj
T*
(multiple labelled graphs, this work adapts the dataset into a node) Tj
T*
(classification task using the 55 nodes inside the generated BGR graph.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Input Data) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The building model is stored in assignment03/obj as four OBJ files:) Tj
T*
0 -18 Td
(Page 1) Tj
ET
endstream
